<div id="bad-email">

<h3>What’s a bad email to send to a freelance prospect?</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>Here’s a great example of an email that gives you no chance of hearing back from a potential client. </p>


<p>"Hi, i’m replying to your post looking for a freelancer."</p>


<p>This person will never hear back because they’ve clearly not taken the time to write a real message. Instead of just shooting off the first email that comes to mind:</p>

<ul>
<li>
	<p>Read the job post carefully and get an idea of the underlying business outcome they need.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Use their website, emails, twitter, and any other background information to learn more about the type of person you’ll be emailing.</p></li>
<li><p>Write a custom, tailored email that is conversational and to the point:</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Start the email off with a first name and a line that shows you actually read their job post.</p></li>
<li><p>Tell them why you are replying to the job post and what you love about their project. </p></li>
<li><p>Don’t talk about your portfolio or experience, instead talk about what a successful project could look like.</p></li>
<li><p>Make it easy for them to reply and get started with the next step. For example, someone should be able to reply “sounds good” to your email.</p></li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
